00053     node_info_t *node_list; /* pointer to a linked list of nodes */
00054     node_info_t *curr_node; /* pointer to the current node when iterating */
00055   }list_head_t;

00090 /******************************************************************************
00091  NAME
00092      HULdestroy_list - Destroys a linked list
00093 
00094  DESCRIPTION
00095     Destroys a linked list created by HULcreate_list().  This function
00096     walks through the list and frees all the nodes, then frees the list head.
00097     Note: this function does not (currently) free the objects in the nodes,
00098     it just leaves 'em hanging.
00099 
00100  RETURNS
00101     Returns SUCCEED/FAIL.
00102 
00103 *******************************************************************************/

00105 );

00110 
00111  DESCRIPTION
00112     Adds an object to the linked list.  If the list is sorted, the comparison

00116  RETURNS
00117     Returns SUCCEED/FAIL.
00118 
00119 *******************************************************************************/
